commText: Ishan Kishan and Rohit are at the crease. Ishan Kishan is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, full and on the pads, came on to the bat very nicely as Ishan Kishan clipped it away with ease through to the square leg ropes

Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, leg byes, FOUR, wrong-line and he pays the price! Full and on the pads, looking for a bit too much swing and it wasn't there, brushed a bit of his pad and went down past Klaasen for four
Bhuvneshwar to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, full and outside off, Ishan Kishan prods forward and steers it down to deep backward point for one
Bhuvneshwar to Rohit, no run, full and outside off, some nice shape back in there, Rohit prods forward looking to knock it into the covers and is beaten

Bhuvneshwar to Rohit, FOUR, down the ground and over the top! Length delivery on off-stump, Rohit skipped down the track and smacked it over mid-on, not the best of timing but more than enough to take it to the ropes
Bhuvneshwar to Rohit, no run, full and angling down leg, Rohit shuffled across looking to flick it away and it just brushed a bit of his pad on its way through to the keeper
Marco Jansen, Left-arm fast, comes into the attack
Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, 5 wides, oh dear, horrible start! Full and way down leg, poor Klaasen didn't even have a chance as it kept going down with the angle
Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, no run, full on off-stump, Ishan Kishan prods forward and blocks it solidly
Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, crunched away! Length delivery outside off, lot of width on offer and Ishan Kishan threw his hands at it, slashed it away up and over backward point

Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, leg byes, FOUR, he's struggling with his line here, good length delivery angling into the pads, too straight again and Ishan Kishan looked to tuck it fine, brushed his thigh pad and went down to the ropes
Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Marco Jansen to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Mayank!! Edged and gone! He's bowled an absolute peach now after those wayward deliveries! Full and straight on middle, he got this to shape away just a touch and Ishan Kishan didn't expect it, looked to clip it into the leg-side and closed the face too early, it caught the leading edge and flew to first slip, great catch from Mayank as it went very quickly. First one down for MI. Ishan Kishan c Mayank b Marco Jansen 9(7) [4s-2]
Naman Dhir, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Marco Jansen to Naman Dhir, no run, full and outside off, Naman Dhir presses forward and drives it to cover

Marco Jansen to Naman Dhir, leg byes, 1 run, back of a length and on the pads, Naman Dhir looks to tuck it into the leg-side and gets struck high on the pad, they pinch a leg-bye as it goes into the off-side
Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, no run, full and just outside off, Naman Dhir pushes it into the off-side tentatively

Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, byes, FOUR, oh jaffa! A good length delivery on off-stump, shaped back in beautifully and caught Naman Dhir on the crease, went past the inside edge and there was too much movement for Klaasen to stop
Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, no run, full on off-stump, knocked towards mid-off

Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, no run, B0$ Good length delivery on off-stump, shapes away a touch this time and Naman Dhir was unsure of his footwork again, he got a thick outside edge and it didn't carry to second slip who'd just been brought in
Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, no run, full on off-stump, knocked towards cover
Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, no run, full and outside off, Naman Dhir presses forward and plays a good looking drive but finds the man at cover
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Rohit, no run, good length delivery on off-stump, Rohit hangs back and bunts it towards mid-on
Cummins to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Rohit, out Caught by Klaasen!! Straight up in the air and taken! Massive wicket for SRH! Length delivery on middle, Rohit looked to pick this up off his hips and flick it away behind square, was just through his shot a touch early and it went straight up in the air off the leading edge. Klaasen called for it very early and took a simple catch in the end. Big blow for MI, they've lost both their openers now. Rohit c Klaasen b Cummins 4(5) [4s-1]
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Cummins to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, that's a jaffa! Good length delivery on off-stump, angles in and nips away off the deck, Suryakumar Yadav was caught on the crease as he looked to defend and was beaten on the outside edge
Still two slips in place

Cummins to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, past the edge again! Length delivery wider outside off, Suryakumar Yadav went searching for this with his bat and had a waft before getting beaten, Test match like line and length!
Rohit Sharma vs Pat Cummins in T20s Inns: 9 Runs: 57 Balls; 41 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 14.25
Cummins to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, three in a row! Good length delivery on off-stump, angles in and nips away, beautifully bowled once more and it went past the outside edge for a third time
Cummins to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, good length delivery on middle-leg, goes straighter and hits his thigh pad as he looks to tuck it into the leg-side. What an over, a wicket-maiden!
MI's opening partnership has not survived the powerplay in 10 out of the 12 games this season.
Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bhuvneshwar to Naman Dhir, out Caught by Marco Jansen!! Edged and a third one goes down! He was troubled by Bhuvneshwar in the last over and he looked to take charge this time, it does not work out! Length delivery outside off, shapes away and he ran at it looking to go up and over, ended up getting a thick edge that went straight to Jansen at 1st slip. He took it at about head-high so it was flying. Excellent new-ball bowling this from SRH. A 9-ball duck for Naman Dhir. Naman Dhir c Marco Jansen b Bhuvneshwar 0(9)

SRH review. Big appeal from everyone around for LBW but it wasn't given. Cummins went upstairs straightaway, could be an inside edge here

Bhuvneshwar to Tilak Varma, leg byes, 1 run, review lost! That was a great shout nonetheless but as it turns out Hawkeye shows it was just pitching outside the leg stump, a good length delivery on leg-stump, angled across but shaped back in, beat the inside edge and hit the top of his pad
Bhuvneshwar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, good length delivery on off-stump, Suryakumar Yadav is right behind that one as he blocks

Bhuvneshwar to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, beautiful shot! Amidst all the great swing bowling, here's a treat to the eyes if you're a fan of batting, pitched up full on off-stump, Suryakumar Yadav pressed forward and creamed that back down the ground past mid-off, excellent timing and balance
Bhuvneshwar to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, full and just outside off, Suryakumar Yadav presses forward and knocks it into the covers

Over summary (1-5) -> An expensive first over by Bhuvneshwar, goes for 13 runs -> Jansen strikes early, Kishan is caught at slip by Agarwal -> A wicket-maiden by Cummins, Rohit is gone -> Naman Dhir walks back to the pavilion without troubling the scorers -> Mumbai Indians in trouble at 36/3 after 5 overs
Now Cummins goes round the wicket

Cummins to Tilak Varma, FOUR, Tilak Varma has had enough! That's a shot of real authority, length delivery just outside off, Tilak Varma ran down the wicket and made a bit of room before slapping that through cover with disdain
Cummins to Tilak Varma, 1 run, full on off-stump, blocked towards mid-on and a fumble allows them to tick the strike over

Cummins to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, in the air and over the ropes! Length delivery on off-stump, Suryakumar Yadav shuffled across looking for one his trademark pick-up shots over fine-leg, it caught the leading edge and went over the third man ropes instead!
Cummins to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, length delivery outside off, cut away to deep backward point for one

T Natarajan to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, a century for the No.1 batter in T20Is! A low full toss on off and Suryakumar Yadav goes down on his knee to loft it over deep extra cover to draw curtains to the game in style. What a fantastic knock. Was struggling while running between the wickets, but with the range of shots in his armoury, nothing is enough to challenge him. A fine, fine victory for the Mumbai Indians!

23:13 Local Time, 17:43 GMT, 23:13 IST: An emphatic victory for Mumbai Indians as they get rid of that bottom spot in the points table. Coming into this game, Sunrisers Hyderabad were the favourites to win because of their performance throughout the season, but the MI boys turned up in front of their home crowd tonight. Head smashed the MI bowlers earlier in the evening, however, skipper Hardik Pandya and spinner Piyush Chawla bagged three wickets each to pull things back. In reply, MI lost three early wickets in the form of Rohit, Kishan and Naman Dhir, however, Surya along with Tilak had an outstanding partnership for the fourth wicket. In the process, SKY also notched up a century as the Mumbai Indians completed the chase within 17.2 overs. Stay around for the presentations..

Pat Cummins | SRH Captain: Probably a couple short, at the Wankhede you want as many as you can get. You always feel like you’re in, the wicket had a little bit in it so we were definitely in the game. I think Sanvir helped us get to that 170 instead of 150, ideally we’d have a bowler. It’s T20 cricket, and it doesn't always work out. SKY played really well. We like playing at home, we’ll wait and see what’s ahead of us. Hopefully a few more fireworks.

Tilak: Initially it was really tough. Both of us were struggling. Wanted to bat with a straight bat. Our plan was to take off the seam. After that we know the 360 degree batter is there. We didn't decide anything. It's a long season. We'll be having such wickets like slow wickets, seaming wickets. I wanted to just play on the situation but it was seaming. But I kept my intent. Was just looking for runs. Wanted to keep my scoring options with the straight bat. Think I batted well. At that moment, he was batting really well so I thought he should be scoring a hundred. So I wanted to take single and not hit big shots.

Hardik Pandya: We want to focus on playing good cricket, still think we gave 10-15 runs extra. The way our batters batted, that was excellent. My bowling, I like to bowl in the right areas, I bowl according to the situation. Bowled in the right areas today and it worked. I was like Chawla had to bowl from the shorter side. He (Chawla) had to be accurate, the margin of errors have become smaller these days for the bowlers. It's unbelievable, the best past of SKY is that he puts the bowlers under pressure. It's sheer confidence, his game has changed, is one of the best batters. He can change a game in a different way, lucky to have him (SKY) in our side.

Suryakumar, Player of the Match: I have done this after a long time. I fielded for 20 overs and batted for 18 overs, only tired (nothing else to worry about.) I feel it was the need of the hour for me. I went out to bat, needed someone to bat till the end. I just enjoyed my time. It's from the Mumbai school of arts, have played a lot of cricket at Wankhede. When the ball stopped seaming, I played all my shots that I practice in the nets. I feel the intent would have been the same, I would have definitely played in the same pattern.

A SKY special lit up the night at the Wankhede. The five-time IPL champions got off the bottom place as a result of that special knock. SRH looked solid at the start of the tournament when their batters were in prime form and going all guns blazing, however, since the time SRH have rested/ dropped Markram, they haven't been able to post such daunting totals. Not sure why they have tinkered with a match-winning combination when it wasn't required. That has only given a chance to other teams in the tournament to climb up the ladder and make sure that the points table becomes interesting. For now, it's goodbye from Nikhil, Sagar, Anurag and Praveen. Good night folks!
